Responsibilities:

Assist in marketing reports preparation and data analysis, gather insights in customer behavior and business trend to improve the performance and drives sales;
Assist the Marketing Manager in the preparation of expense report, cost and budget report;
Work closely with marketing and sales departments in launching new product programs and execution and completion of projects;
Develop the marketing plan for products that support in conjunction with Sales & Marketing team, including key activities and budgets to support the acquisition of new customers and retention of existing customers;
Collaborate with various internal and external parties to ensure smooth execution of event promotion and operation.
Requirements:

Degree holder in Marketing, Business Administration, or other related discipline;
Minimum 3 years of working experience in marketing or sales related discipline;
Work experience in HORECA, Frozen Meat and food Trading business is an advantage;
Experience in Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, Wechat, and search engine marketing is a plus but not a must;
Proficient in PC applications, including MS Word, PowerPoint and Excel;

Creative and well-organized with excellent analytical and problem-solving skills;
Excellent communication and presentation skills;
Able to excel in fast-paced and dynamic environment with tight deadlines;
Self-motivated, result-oriented team player;
Proficient in Chinese and English.

We offer competitive remuneration and fringe benefits including discretionary bonus, medical insurance, annual leave and 5-day work. Interested party please send detailed resume in both Chinese and English version with expected salary & date of availability by clicking "Apply Now".

Personal data will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Responsibilities

Create, execute and coordinate marketing program materials, communications, graphics, brand website maintenance, digital/social media strategy and events/exhibitions;
Execute social media marketing ad strategies on Instagram, Facebook, LinkedIn, Pinterest Twitter and YouTube;
Manage and maintain website content using HTML or other web content management interface;
Prepare media plan, budget summary and execute advertisement campaign with reports;
Report on the performance of different paid media platform and provide campaign insights to assess campaign effectiveness and identify optimization opportunities;
Coordinate with Design, PR and Communications and other functional teams to ensure brand consistency and smoothness operations;
Other ad hoc tasks as assigned.

 Requirements

Degree holder in marketing or related disciplines; 
3 years or above experiences in digital marketing;
Knowledge in Google Adwords / Facebook AD manager is an advantage;
Knowledge of Photoshop or AI is an advantage;
Good communication in spoken and written English and Chinese and Mandarin;
Immediate available is preferred.

Tasks and Responsibilities

Responsible for analyzing the market of HUTCHMED products and therapeutic areas.  Analyze, coordinate and support the information needs of preparing new product launch;
Formulate integrated go-to-market plan of HUTCHMED products and launch tactics to maximize overall opportunity;
Define, monitor and achieve key performance metrics in achieving milestone to inform strategy and support execution;
Intellectual curiosity about all aspects of our customers and business with a strong desire to persist in finding opportunities to maximize our business;
Structured thinker and critical problem-solver; ability to distill and synthesize complex information from various resources to actionable insights;
Ability to anticipate and rapidly respond to market and competitive changes in developing and executing brand strategies;
Proactively monitor external data, publications and their impact on future treatment algorithms, as well as potential impact on guidelines and pathways;
Develop annual budget and track expenses through the year;
Experience successfully working in cross functional matrix teams; 
Ability to challenge the status quo with good rationale and logic; being provocative and creative in a productive fashion;
Maintain strong compliance with all relevant internal policies, compliance and legal requirements.

 Experience & Requirements

Minimum of 5 years solid experience in pharmaceutical industry with experience in new product launch;
Bachelor Degree or above in Science;
Marketing experience including strategy development and tactical execution;
Excellent interpersonal skill with the ability to build working relations both internally and externally;
Strong verbal and written communications skills;
Strong commercial orientation and business acumen;
Strength managing complexity and multiple competing priorities;
Experience influencing without direct authority and working successfully with cross-functional teams and multiple agency partners;
A creative and dynamic team player with strategic and marketing sense;
Experience in oncology (and immunology) areas is preferred;
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Job title is subjected to the candidate’s qualification and experience.



Salary and benefits will be commensurate with experience. Please send detailed resume with current and expected salary by clicking “APPLY NOW” in the below.

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. The information provided will be treated in strict confidence and used only for consideration of application for relevant/similar post(s) within the CK Hutchison Group of Companies. Applicants not having heard from us within four weeks from the date of this advertisement may consider their application unsuccessful. All personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed after the recruitment exercise when no longer required.

Smart Charge, a new service brand run by HKT and CLP, aims to offer one-stop and hassle-free electric vehicle (EV) charging solutions for end-users and commercial entities in Hong Kong to meet the increasing market demand. 

It is a challenging and dynamic opportunity for an all rounded marketer to work for this brand which is striving for differentiation and continual growth. 

Your role:

Explore partnership opportunities / initiatives and manage day-to-day partnership operations and logistics;
Nurture long term relationships with key strategic partners to foster consistent support to Smart Living products via joint promotions or events, including lead generation events and external corporate events;
Build and manage scalable partnership programs to drive broad adoption of Smart Charge products and services;
Collaborate with various internal and external parties for planning and executing marketing campaigns, including the planning and execution of operation logistic , advertising and communication tools from concept to implementation;
Ensure marketing messages are synchronized across different business units and monitor  marketing campaigns to ensure communications are streamlined and aligned;
Stay informed of news and marketing activities in  relevant markets.  

To succeed in this role:

University graduate in Marketing, Communications, Business Administration or related disciplines;
Minimum 8 years working experience in Product or Service Marketing and/or related field;
Proven track record of driving partnership strategy, preferably in luxury product industry, prestige members clubs and automotive industries;
Strong business acumen with exceptional logical thinking, highly motivated and presentable
Demonstrated initiative and problem solving skills with a service focus
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with ability to work effectively and cross-functionally with people at all levels
Knowledge or interest in automobile industry
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Cantonese
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Assistant Vice President

If you have the desire for an exciting and rewarding career, please send us your resume immediately, quoting the reference number, your present and expected salary via email to Human Resources.

REQUIREMENTS

Diploma or above in marketing, communications or related disciplines
2-3 years relevant experience, preferably in retail or digital marketing
Familiar with social media networks with online copywriting experience
Strong knowledge in Google Ads and Google Analytics
Good communication and presentation skill in English and Chinese
Proficient PC skills (e.g. MS office, Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese Word Processing)

RESPONSIBILITIES:

Responsible for developing the marketing plan and strategy; compiling and monitoring the annual promotion and marketing budget plan;

Assist the Operation team in formulating in-store marketing and promotional activities to drive sales & traffic;
Align with the company strategy and objectives, initiate and implement relevant social media platforms such as Website, Facebook & Instagram, etc;
Work closely with various parties for planning and executing marketing campaigns, including organizing events, preparing sales materials, advertising and communication tools;
Develop monthly report and monitor the sales performance of marketing activities;
Explore joint promotion opportunity with other parties;
Carry out ad-hoc tasks as assigned by management.

We offer competitive package including 5-day work, public holiday & medical scheme together with career growth opportunities. Interested parties, please send full resume and expected salary and recent portfolio to Personnel & Administration Department.

The Role
We are looking for a creative, passionate and enthusiastic PR and Marketing Executive to join our team. You will have a chance to work at a fast-paced mission driven company that brings material science to life and benefit the mass. We are bringing business disruption and new hygiene standard to the world with the introduction of new photocatalyst products and services. With the continuous R&D and business innovation, we are thrilled to develop the next generation technology that safeguards everyday life.

Responsibilities


Assist to plan, coordinate and implement marketing programs;
Day-to-day management of media plans, reports and follow up on materials;
Produce competitive analysis and reports for the relevant consumer and business sectors;
Support and work closely with the team on buying executions on a day-to-day basis;
Develop engaging, creative content for our social media & e-commerce platform (Including writing, editing and proofreading of the product description, social media feeds, advertising collaterals, SEO contents, etc.);
Assist in marketing reports preparation and data analysis, gather insights in customer behavior and business trends to improve the performance and drive sales.

Requirements


University degree holder in Marketing, Communications, Creative Media, Business or related disciplines;
1-2 years relevant experience in FMCG/healthcare. Agency background is an advantage;
Proficiency in using Facebook, Instagram, WeChat, Weibo and others to build communities and enhance brand profile;
Strong market sense and good creativity;
Patient, pay attention to details and with good communication skills;
Good command in both written and spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin.

We offer the right candidate attractive remuneration package and outstanding prospects for career advancement and development.  The right candidate will progress career in a forward thinking and dynamic business with exciting growth plans.  If you are qualified and interested, please send your full resume with current & expected salary and availability by clicking "APPLY".

All information collected will be treated as strictly confidential and used for recruitment purposes only. (Only shortlisted candidates will be notified)

Responsibilities

Drive sales to achieve company's assigned sales target;
Develop strategy and content for digital marketing & social media platforms across different markets and to evaluate effectiveness of different marketing campaigns;
Perform sales analysis and gather market information for sales and marketing strategies' formulation;
Plan & execute marketing activities for assigned product portfolio to increase brand awareness, expand customer base, engagement and achieve sales target;
Monitor and maintain good relationship with existing distributors to maximize sales and profits;
Proactively develop new distribution channels to ensure continuous business growth and expand market coverage;
Manage internal designers & work closely with third parties for advertisements' production;
Monitoring A&P expenditure & product budget;
Organize and support exhibitions, events & brand activities year-round
Support ad-hoc projects and marketing activities as assigned.

Requirements

University degree holder in Marketing / Health Technology / Nutriology / Biology Chemistry or related discipline;  candidate with science background is preferable
Experience in digital marketing and social media marketing is a must
Creative, detail oriented, outgoing and result-oriented with excellent interpersonal communication skill;
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese (Mandarin is an asset);
Able to work under pressure with multi-tasking skill, willing to learn;
High sense of responsibility, mature and self-initiative;
Excellent PC skills;

Interested parties please apply in full resume including current and expected salary by clicking 'Apply Now'. To know more about us, please visit our company website at http://www.healthbank.com.hk.

All information received will be kept in strict confidence and only be used for employment-related purposes.

CHINA MOBILE HONG KONG COMPANY LIMITED ("CMHK") is the wholly-owned subsidiary of China Mobile Limited (HKEx: 941) (NYSE: CHL), which ranks 65th on the Fortune Global 500.

Our company strives to offer superior service experience and to become the preferable digital partner for customers. We are preserving an environment with trust, responsibility and caring. At CMHK, we commit to maximizing people’s potential and paving the way toward success for every striver. We are now inviting high caliber professional to join us.

Division: Marketing  / Smart Home Business Department

In this position, you will:

Responsible for the design and delivery of household product solutions;
Promote ecological cooperation and product expansion and cooperation; have practical experience in building a smart furniture ecosystem, have strong upstream terminal or application field customer resources, and be able to quickly build a product system based on the industrial chain;
Responsible for the B2B2C product integration planning, and cooperate with the corporate sales department to participate in the project competition of real estate developers and industry customers, and formulate product plans;
The ability to understand the business goals and high-level requirements and effectively define a systematic solution;
Responsible for technology solution of home service IT supporting system, smart home products, GPON/IP network enhancement.
As technical facial point, create quality deliverables and communicate with appropriate all level audiences;
Candidate shall coordinate various projects which related to home service IT supporting system, new products release, network enhancement.



To be successful in this position, you should meet the following requirements:

Bachelor degree holder;
CAPM/ITIL/PMP certification preferred;
At least 5 years of work experience;
Excellent communication skills, presentation skills, leadership skills and good at teamwork;
Energetic, self-motivated, able to work under pressure and independently;
Good computer skills in Microsoft Office;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese/Putonghua.
Candidate with less experience may consider as Assistant Manager

When you work:

5 days work
8 hours/day

What you enjoy:

Double pay
Discretionary Performance bonus
Life insurance
Medical insurance
Education subsidies
Birthday gift
Marriage leave
Birthday leave
Staff discount

CMHK is committed to be an equal opportunity employer. We offer exceptional benefits package and the opportunity to work in a challenging environment. Personal data provided by applicants will be treated strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only.

Job Responsibilities

Plan and organize membership programs including Seminars, Dinner Reception and Trade Matching programs, etc;

To conduct project management, and event coordination / supervision;
Manage FB and IG accounts;
To provide administrative support to the department;

Job Requirements

University graduate with at least 2 years working experience; 
A good team player with strong communication skills and service-oriented minds;
Initiative and detail-minded with good sense of responsibility;
Good writing skills in both English and Chinese;
Able to speak fluent English, Cantonese and Putonghua;
Proficient with MS Office, knowing of Chinese typing is a must;
Basic photo and video editing skill;
Candidates with less experience will be considered as Senior Marketing Assistant.
Immediate available is preferred.

We offer competitive remuneration and all applications will be treated in strict confidence. If your profile matches the above requirements, please send your full resume including your last and expected salary to us.

Data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

About our client
A Fast-growing Global Biotechnology company, its headquarter is in Hong Kong with offices in APAC & Europe, who is seeking a NEW Team Head about talent acquisition & employer branding, reports to the Chief People Officer (Global).

Energetic, move fast and variety of recruiting methods
Corporate in-house + Agency experience is preferred
Fluent English and Chinese Speaking
Comfortable with some hands-on operations

Responsibilities


Formulate and implement disruptive talent acquisition strategies and build talent pipeline for future organization growth;
Oversee a team of passionate talent acquisition specialists and full cycle recruiting processes;
Spearhead our employer brand building with an aim to make it a global brand, while bringing awareness to local communities and networks;
Drive talent and business outcomes as a manpower and organisation structure advisor & HRBP to the company;
Create a game changing and technology driven innovative talent acquisition processes and candidate experience.
Requirements
Previous experience leading a Talent Acquisition function for an international company, with agency experience is a plus;

Proven track record of success in high growth organization with a variety of recruiting methods including direct sourcing, social recruiting and traditional methods, experience in Biotechnology / Life-Sciences recruitment is a plus;
Rich experience in building employer brand supported by positive business outcome;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English & Chinese;
Comfortable with hands-on tasks and fast-paced working environment.
To apply, please click on the ‘Apply Now’ button or contact Nick Chow at (852) 3502-2637 for a confidential discussion. Alternatively, email your resume (with your notice period, current and expected salary) to nick.chow@macleansgroup .com

Your interest will be treated in strict confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified.
